CONTRIBUTING.md
     3Ôćĺ# Contributing ÔÇŽ
     5Ôćĺ## Code of Conduct
     7ÔćĺAll interactions in the **npm** organization on GitHub are considered to be covered by our standard [Code of Conduct](https://docs.npmjs.com/policies/conduct).
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ## Reporting Bugs
    11ÔćĺBefore submitting a new bug report please search for an existing or similar report.
    12Ôćĺ
    13ÔćĺUse one of our existing issue templates if you believe you've come across a unique problem.
    14Ôćĺ
    15ÔćĺDuplicate issues, or issues that don't use one of our templates may get closed without a response.
    16Ôćĺ
    17Ôćĺ## Pull Request Conventions
    19Ôćĺ### Commits
    21ÔćĺWe use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).
    22Ôćĺ
    23ÔćĺWhen opening a pull request please be sure that either the pull request title, or each commit in the pull request, has one of the following prefixes:
    24Ôćĺ
    25Ôćĺ - `feat`: For when introducing a new feature.  The result will be a new semver minor version of the package when it is next published.
    26Ôćĺ - `fix`: For bug fixes. The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    27Ôćĺ - `docs`: For documentation updates.  The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    28Ôćĺ - `chore`: For changes that do not affect the published module.  Often these are changes to tests.  The result will be *no* change to the version of the package when it is next published (as the commit does not affect the published version).
    29Ôćĺ
    30Ôćĺ### Test Coverage
    32ÔćĺPull requests made against this repo will run `npm test` automatically.  Please make sure tests pass locally before submitting a PR.
    33Ôćĺ
    34ÔćĺEvery new feature or bug fix should come with a corresponding test or tests that validate the solutions. Testing also reports on code coverage and will fail if code coverage drops.
    35Ôćĺ
    36Ôćĺ### Linting
    38ÔćĺLinting is also done automatically once tests pass.  `npm run lintfix` will fix most linting errors automatically.
    39Ôćĺ
    40ÔćĺPlease make sure linting passes before submitting a PR.
    41Ôćĺ
    42Ôćĺ## What _not_ to contribute?
    44Ôćĺ### Dependencies
    46ÔćĺIt should be noted that our team does not accept third-party dependency updates/PRs.  If you submit a PR trying to update our dependencies we will close it with or without a reference to these contribution guidelines.
    47Ôćĺ
    48Ôćĺ### Tools/Automation
    50ÔćĺOur core team is responsible for the maintenance of the tooling/automation in this project and we ask contributors to not make changes to these when contributing (e.g. `.github/*`, `.eslintrc.json`, `.licensee.json`).  Most of those files also have a header at the top to remind folks they are automatically generated.  Pull requests that alter these will not be accepted.

README.md
     4Ôćĺ## Note
     6Ôćĺ-   Sections are treated as nested objects.
     7Ôćĺ
     8Ôćĺ-   Section-less items are treated as globals.
     9Ôćĺ
    10Ôćĺ## Usage
    12ÔćĺConsider an INI file such as the following:
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ```ini
    15Ôćĺ; This comment is being ignored
    16Ôćĺscope = global
    17Ôćĺ
    18Ôćĺ[database]
    19Ôćĺuser = dbuser
    20Ôćĺpassword = dbpassword
    21Ôćĺdatabase = use_this_database
    22Ôćĺ
    23Ôćĺ[paths.default]
    24Ôćĺdatadir = /var/lib/data
    25Ôćĺarray[] = first value
    26Ôćĺarray[] = second value
    27Ôćĺarray[] = third value
    28Ôćĺ```
    29Ôćĺ
    30ÔćĺYou can **read**, **modify** and **write** it like so:
    31Ôćĺ
    32Ôćĺ```js
    33Ôćĺimport { writeFile , readFile } from 'node:fs/promises'
    34Ôćĺimport { stringify , parse } from 'ini'
    35Ôćĺ
    36Ôćĺ//  Read INI file as text
    37Ôćĺ
    38Ôćĺlet text = await readFile(`./Original.ini`,{
    39Ôćĺ    encoding : 'utf-8'
    40Ôćĺ})
    41Ôćĺ
    42Ôćĺ//  Parse text data to object
    43Ôćĺ
    44Ôćĺconst config = parse(text)
    45Ôćĺ
    46Ôćĺ//  Modify data object
    47Ôćĺ
    48Ôćĺconfig.scope = 'local'
    49Ôćĺconfig.database.database = 'use_another_database'
    50Ôćĺconfig.paths.default.tmpdir = '/tmp'
    51Ôćĺdelete config.paths.default.datadir
    52Ôćĺconfig.paths.default.array.push('fourth value')
    53Ôćĺ
    54Ôćĺ//  Stringify data object
    55Ôćĺ
    56Ôćĺtext = stringify(config,{ 
    57Ôćĺ    section : 'section' 
    58Ôćĺ})
    59Ôćĺ
    60Ôćĺ//  Write INI file as text
    61Ôćĺ
    62Ôćĺawait writeFile(`./Modified.ini`,text)
    63Ôćĺ```
    64Ôćĺ
    65ÔćĺThe written file will contain the following:
    66Ôćĺ
    67Ôćĺ```ini
    68Ôćĺ[section]
    69Ôćĺscope=local
    70Ôćĺ[section.database]
    71Ôćĺuser=dbuser
    72Ôćĺpassword=dbpassword
    73Ôćĺdatabase=use_another_database
    74Ôćĺ[section.paths.default]
    75Ôćĺtmpdir=/tmp
    76Ôćĺarray[]=first value
    77Ôćĺarray[]=second value
    78Ôćĺarray[]=third value
    79Ôćĺarray[]=fourth value
    80Ôćĺ```
    81Ôćĺ
    82Ôćĺ## API
    84Ôćĺ### Parse
    86ÔćĺAttempts to turn the given INI string into a nested data object.
    87Ôćĺ
    88Ôćĺ```js
    89Ôćĺ// You can also use `decode`
    90Ôćĺconst object = parse(`<INI Text>`) 
    91Ôćĺ```
    92Ôćĺ
    93Ôćĺ### Stringify
    95ÔćĺEncodes the given data object as an INI formatted string.
    96Ôćĺ
    97Ôćĺ```js
    98Ôćĺ// You can also use `encode`
    99Ôćĺstringify(object,{
   100Ôćĺ
   101Ôćĺ    /**
   102Ôćĺ     *  Whether to insert spaces before & after `=`
   103Ôćĺ     * 
   104Ôćĺ     *  Disabled by default to have better 
   105Ôćĺ     *  compatibility with old picky parsers.
   106Ôćĺ     */
   107Ôćĺ
   108Ôćĺ    whitespace : false ,
   109Ôćĺ
   110Ôćĺ    /**
   111Ôćĺ     *  Whether to align the `=` character for each section.
   112Ôćĺ     *  -> Also enables the `whitespace` option
   113Ôćĺ     */
   114Ôćĺ
   115Ôćĺ    align : false ,
   116Ôćĺ
   117Ôćĺ    /**
   118Ôćĺ     *  Identifier to use for global items 
   119Ôćĺ     *  and to prepend to all other sections.
   120Ôćĺ     */
   121Ôćĺ
   122Ôćĺ    section ,
   123Ôćĺ
   124Ôćĺ    /**
   125Ôćĺ     *  Whether to sort all sections & their keys alphabetically.
   126Ôćĺ     */
   127Ôćĺ
   128Ôćĺ    sort : false ,
   129Ôćĺ
   130Ôćĺ    /**
   131Ôćĺ     *  Whether to insert a newline after each section header.
   132Ôćĺ     * 
   133Ôćĺ     *  The TOSHIBA & FlashAir parser require this format. 
   134Ôćĺ     */
   135Ôćĺ
   136Ôćĺ    newline : false ,
   137Ôćĺ
   138Ôćĺ    /**
   139Ôćĺ     *  Which platforms line-endings should be used.
   140Ôćĺ     * 
   141Ôćĺ     *  win32 -> CR+LF
   142Ôćĺ     *  other -> LF
   143Ôćĺ     * 
   144Ôćĺ     *  Default is the current platform
   145Ôćĺ     */
   146Ôćĺ
   147Ôćĺ    platform ,
   148Ôćĺ
   149Ôćĺ    /**
   150Ôćĺ     *  Whether to append `[]` to array keys.
   151Ôćĺ     * 
   152Ôćĺ     *  Some parsers treat duplicate names by themselves as arrays
   153Ôćĺ     */
   154Ôćĺ
   155Ôćĺ    bracketedArray : true
   156Ôćĺ
   157Ôćĺ})
   158Ôćĺ```
   159Ôćĺ
   160Ôćĺ*For backwards compatibility any string passed as the*  
   161Ôćĺ*options parameter is treated as the `section` option.*
   162Ôćĺ
   163Ôćĺ```js
   164Ôćĺstringify(object,'section')
   165Ôćĺ```
   166Ôćĺ
   167Ôćĺ### Un / Escape
   169ÔćĺTurn the given string into a safe to  
   170Ôćĺuse key or value in your INI file.
   171Ôćĺ
   172Ôćĺ```js
   173Ôćĺsafe(`"unsafe string"`) // -> \"unsafe string\"
   174Ôćĺ```
   175Ôćĺ
   176ÔćĺOr reverse the process with:
   177Ôćĺ
   178Ôćĺ```js
   179Ôćĺunsafe(`\\"safe string\\"`) // -> "safe string"
   180Ôćĺ```

